# Web Page Testing Methodology

## Overview

Use the **cursor-browser-extension** MCP server to perform automated Chrome browser testing of web applications.

## MCP Browser Tools

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `browser_navigate` | Navigate to a URL |
| `browser_click` | Click elements by ref ID |
| `browser_fill_form` | Fill form inputs |
| `browser_type` | Type text into focused element |
| `browser_wait_for` | Wait for time or element |
| `browser_snapshot` | Get current page state |
| `browser_take_screenshot` | Capture visual screenshot |
| `browser_console_messages` | Check for JS errors |

## Gatekeeper URLs

- Login page: `http://localhost:5050/login.html`
- Health: `http://localhost:5050/health`
- API base: `http://localhost:5050/api`

## Testing Workflow

1. Navigate to page (e.g. login.html)
2. Use refs from snapshot to interact (click, fill form)
3. Wait after dynamic content
4. Verify snapshot / console for errors
5. Take screenshot when needed

## Test Categories

- **Page load**: Login page, health endpoint
- **Interactive**: Login form, tabs (password / magic link)
- **API**: Auth endpoints (login, refresh, me)
- **Console**: No JS errors

## Best Practices

- Use refs from the most recent snapshot
- Wait after clicks for dynamic content
- Check console for JS errors
- Document PASS/FAIL per test
